    bmd_fix_brake_inspect_tip: "Quiet braking tests better than visual — brakes that squeal or pulse often signal contamination, not wear.",
    // fix_tire_pressure_inspect
    bmd_fix_tire_pressure_inspect_title: "Check Tire Pressure",
    bmd_fix_tire_pressure_inspect_tool_1: "Pump with gauge (floor pump preferred)",
    bmd_fix_tire_pressure_inspect_step_1: "Know your target PSI. Road: 80–100 (skinnier tires = higher). Gravel: 35–50. Mountain XC: 22–28. Mountain trail/enduro: 18–24. Commuter: 60–80. Check sidewall for manufacturer's min/max if unsure",
    bmd_fix_tire_pressure_inspect_step_2: "Check when tires are cold (before riding) — air expands when warm and gives a false-high reading",
    bmd_fix_tire_pressure_inspect_step_3: "Unscrew valve cap; for Presta, also unscrew the small top nut until it clicks up",
    bmd_fix_tire_pressure_inspect_step_4: "Press pump head on straight, clamp the lever — check gauge before adding air",
    bmd_fix_tire_pressure_inspect_step_5: "Rider weight matters: heavier rider = top of the range, lighter rider = bottom. Tubeless: drop 5–10 PSI from tubed equivalent",
